laboratory_examinations.findings: No pleural or pericardial effusions; liver, gallbladder, adrenal glands, spleen unremarkable; mild diffuse atrophy of the pancreas; small hiatal hernia; multiple tiny retroperitoneal lymph nodes do not meet CT criteria for significant adenopathy; extensive sigmoid diverticulosis; no drainable fluid collections or evidence of perforation.
Creatinine elevated, intravenous contrast was deferred due to elevated creatinine.
